Worker mandibles (
Fig. 28B
): With typical xylophagous pattern. Left mandible: apical tooth slightly larger than M1+2, M3 easily recognizable, with marked cutting edge between marginal teeth; molar tooth hidden by molar prominence; molar prominence with marked ridges. Right mandible: apical tooth larger than M1, M2 easily recognizable, with marked posterior cutting edge, and molar plate with four marked ridges.

